SIMPLE: resource
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resource
<hw>Re*source"</hw> <pr>(r?*s?rs")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>ressource</ets>, fr. OF. <ets>ressourdre</ets>,
<ets>resourdre</ets>, to spring forth or up again; pref. <ets>re-</ets>
re- + <ets>sourdre</ets> to spring forth. See <er>Source</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>That to which one resorts orr on which one depends for
supply or support; means of overcoming a difficulty; resort;
expedient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Threat'nings mixed with prayers, his last <qex>resource</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Pecuniary means; funds; money, or
any property that can be converted into supplies; available means or
capabilities of any kind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Scotland by no means escaped the fate ordained for every country
which is connected, but not incorporated, with another country of
greater <qex>resources</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Expedient; resort; means; contrivance.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resourceful</ent>⟦br⟧
